Business Brief -- Federal Home Loan Mortgage:
   Profit More Than Doubled
   During the Fourth Quarter
The company's revenue base, called net interest margin,
grew 13% to $388 million from $342 million. The growth was
paced by a 24% increase in management and guarantee fees
collected from mortgage lenders to guarantee the securities
and a 23% increase in profit on mortgages purchased and
retained in the company's own portfolio.
   Mortgage loan charge-offs rose 5% to $81 million from $77
million in the third quarter. Freddie Mac's proportion of
single-family loans that were 90 days or more past due was
0.59%, up from 0.57% the previous quarter.
   Freddie Mac dropped $3 to $130 in New York Stock Exchange
trading.